statically allocated memory = memory that is allocated at compile time
- global and static variables
- arrays (not the ones that are malloced) 
    e.g. int array[10] = {0};
- strings 

compile a c program -> assembly -> executable (a.out)

 __________
|          |    
| Memory   |   
 ----------

1. Load the value / variable from memory into a register 
2. Modify the value 
3. Save the value back into memory 